  "text": "On the other hand, several works on the B formalism proposed tightened modularity constraints for ensuring the absence of inconsistency or extending the formalism for allowing some useful kinds of sharing. The already mentioned in Sect. 2.1 works in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] are still situated in the single-writer paradigm. Assuming the CSP controllers can be viewed as a single B entity, the modularity constraints would allow the architectures (a) and (b) of Fig. 5 , because of the clear separation of the seeing (read-only) paths and the importing (read-write) paths. These tightened modularity constraints were quickly integrated into the B commercial tools.",
